Corsair has launched its new compact K63 mechanical keyboard with Cherry MX Red switches. The keyboard sports a lightweight tenkeyless design, making it ideal for travelling gamers or set-ups with limited desk space. The Cherry MX Red mechanical switches feature gold contacts for increased durability and 100% anti-ghosting key rollover. Backlighting comprises of per-key red LED lighting and the keyboard includes a Windows key lock control, allowing you to disable the Windows key when playing games. The compact keyboard is priced at €79 on Corsair’s website.   